"Publish own Own Site, Syndicate Elsewhere" is the practice of publishing to your own website then publishing the same content to third-party platforms. 

For example, if I post a zettel to my gartenkasten, _then_ post the text of that zettel to BlueSky or Facebook, then I am following POSSE. 

One benefit of this is you'll [**Prev**:: [[Thinking/Zettels/(5A1A) Record To Make Findable\|make your ideas findable]]]. And you own the platform on which your content is being posted. (Which is why everyone says to start an email list, I guess.)

This flips the typical practice: you post on social media then... that's it. 

[**source**:: [POSSE - IndieWeb](https://indieweb.org/POSSE)]
